comment: I forgot the oak.   Nice hint of roast, and dry.   Of course, estery Englishy yeast shows through.  Malty - I should've entered this fucker in whatever contest that LHBS was collecting for a week ago when I bought ingredients for that APA I brewed last weekend.

Fits the BJCP2008 style guides to a "T".  
Primarily malty-yeasty with roasty character.   Muted hops, low end fruity esters.   Damn........
